SHIMER v. RONK. (Supreme Court, Appellate Division, Second Department. June 10, 1910.) Appeal from Municipal Court, Borough of Brooklyn. Action by Lillian E. Shimer against Martha E. Ronk. From a judgment for plaintiff, defendant appeals, and plaintiff moves to dismiss. Motion granted.

Argued before JBNKS, BURR, THOMAS, RICH, and CARR, JJ.

Robert H. Wilson, for appellant. Henry Brill, for respondent. PER CURIAM.

Motion to dismiss appeal granted, without costs. See Shimer v. Ronk (decided herewith) 123 N. Y. Supp. 479.
